>Bamford's book "The Puzzle Palace" was about the NSA.

But Bamford misused that for the NSA probably because he thought it was
cute. At the time his book was published The Pentagon was what was referred
to as "The Puzzle Palace".

>On the other hand, how long ago were you in the Navy?  
>No Such Agency was based in the Pentagon until it moved to Ft. Meade
>sometime around 1954.

Inaccurate on both counts. NSA was at a number of classified locations
around Washington D.C., and little of it was in the Pentagon. They didn't
move to Meade until a few years later than 1954.

